          </a>
          <div class="caption"> <h2>Los Cinco Soles</h2></div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-lg-8 text-left">
            <p class="caption border2">One of the great things about our private tour is that you get to see Cozumel as it suits you best, according to your interests and what you feel like along the way! Moreover, our tours have a minimum charge for the first 3 hours and afterward you can add more time at an extra fee so you can decide what sites to visit and how much time you spend at each site.
For example a 4 hour tour could be something like having the driver pick you up at the hotel or cruise ship pier, do a city tour where the driver takes you to local landmarks and tells you all about Cozumel's history and some fun facts,afterward make your way to San Gervasio Mayan ruins and then head to the "wild" side of the island for a drive down the coastal highway (breathtaking views!) where you could stop along the way for pictures and have a nice lunch at one of the ocean front restaurants along the highway and afterward head back to the hotel or ship. </p>
